{{Quote|Okay, Cherit's outfit supplied rak, lxetallic, and Twi'lek girls to some minor Kuati nobs. He was doing his deals here for a while. Maybe he was muscling in on your relative's turf.|[[Unidentified barkeeper (Paradise Cantina)|A bartender]] to the [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]] [[Boba Fett/Legends|Boba Fett]]|<ref name="Legacy of the Force: Sacrifice">''[[Legacy of the Force: Sacrifice]]''</ref>}}
Before his [[Death/Legends|death]] around the [[Standard year/Legends|year]] [[40 ABY/Legends|40 ABY]], a gang boss named [[Cherit]] provided [[Kuati/Legends|Kuati]] nobles with a substance called '''lxetallic'''. A [[Gender/Legends|man]] named [[L. Fraig]] took over [[Cherit's gang|Cherit's operation]] after he died.

==Behind the scenes==
Rak was briefly mentioned in [[2007]]'s ''[[Legacy of the Force: Sacrifice]]'', a novel by [[Karen Traviss]].

